      "action": "journal-upsert",
      "id": "v41-holders-15",
      "strategy_id": "v41-holders-15",
      "cohort_label": "v41",
      "hypothesis": "Holder threshold sweep - lowest cutoff. Filters out only the bottom 6.7% of the universe (<15 holders). Hypothesis: tokens with <10 holders (4.3% of population) are the truly thin-LP rug-prone cases - excluding them removes high-variance tails without sacrificing meaningful coverage. Expected volume: ~93-95% of v25 baseline (largest sample size in the cohort). If this variant matches or barely beats v25, the very-thin-holder tail is small enough that filtering it doesn't move the needle on aggregate P&L. Best as the 'permissive control' for the cohort.",
      "prediction": {
