      "cohort_label": "v41",
      "hypothesis": "Holder threshold sweep - the cap. Keeps ONLY tokens that hit the holder_count cap at 19 (~93% of v25's universe). This is effectively a binary 'did getTokenLargestAccounts return at least 19 non-infrastructure accounts' filter - functionally equivalent to 'token has enough holders to fill the top-20 RPC slice'. Since 18 of 20 v25 worst losers had holder_count=19, this threshold does NOT cut the loss tail by much. Expected: very close to v25 baseline performance. The value of this variant is as a comparison anchor for the lower thresholds - if 15/16/17 substantially beat 19, the small <19 tail is disproportionately loss-prone. If 19 beats them, the metric is just noise and tighter is better.",
